title: Fresh blood to make NRL impact in 2016
text:
Fresh blood from 20s, NSW and Queensland Cup to make NRL impact in 2016 Nathan Ryan FOX SPORTS Fresh blood from 20s, NSW and Queensland Cup to make NRL impact in 2016 Nathan Ryan FOX SPORTS The NRL draft merry-go-round 2:13 
NRL: The NRL hasn't quite grasped the draft concept like the AFL, as 2015 proved to be a season filled with big name players controversially signing to join other clubs. October 7th 2015 /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/NRL/ 
EACH season the game unearths a hidden gem who catches everyone by surprise. 
In 2015 the likes of Jack Bird and Tom Trbojevic emerged from the shadows, playing beyond their years in their first season of NRL. 
You can rest assured 2016 will be no different, with the next crop of young guns hungry to make an impact and push their way into first grade. 
And it’s not just the Holden Cup you need to look out for, with NSW and Queensland Cup set to unleash a host of talent into the competition next season. 
Looking over the roster of all 16 teams, we’ve come up with a list of fresh faces to keep an eye out for ahead of 2016. This week on the Market Watch podcast Cowboys general manager of football Peter Parr joins Brett Kimmorley, Ben Glover and Nathan Ryan for all the grand final wash up and a look ahead to the health of every roster for 2016.
